tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated total cholesterol and triglycerides, indicating dyslipidemia, and mildly increased LDL. Creatinine results are inconsistent (one high, one low), but if elevated, may suggest impaired renal function. Total CO₂ is slightly low, possibly reflecting mild metabolic acidosis. Glucose and HbA1c are within normal limits. Liver function, electrolytes, and protein levels are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation for renal function and cardiovascular risk assessment, and consider repeat creatinine testing to clarify renal status.
